<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4499] CassandraStorage allow_deletes doesn&apos;t work in Hadoop cluster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4499</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using CassandraStorage in a Pig script that runs in a Hadoop cluster, the environment variable configuration option for allow_deletes doesn&apos;t work.  I&apos;d like to see allow_deletes added as a URL parameter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, I&apos;d like to do&lt;br/&gt;
STORE storable_events INTO &apos;cassandra://drlcrs/event?allow_deletes=true&apos; USING org.apache.cassandra.hadoop.pig.CassandraStorage();&lt;/p&gt;</description>
